Global mitigation effort

This lever sets how the rest of the world may decarbonise.

  • Ambition Level 1

    The rest of the world does not make any changes.

  • Ambition Level 2

    The rest of the world increases their ambitions to reduce emissions and thus shift to a pathway which would lead to 3.2°C of global warming.

  • Ambition Level 3

    The rest of the world increases their ambitions to reduce emissions and thus shift to a pathway which would lead to 2.0°C of global warming.

  • Ambition Level 4

    The rest of the world increases their ambitions to reduce emissions and thus shift to a pathway which would lead to 1.5°C of global warming.

For more details on the definition of the ambition levels for this lever and on the context and modelling assumptions, please refer to the technical documentation.
